<%#
  Email-change-pending modal — opened via
  $store.modals.open('email-change-pending', { currentEmail, newEmail }).
  Rendered inside studio/_modal_host, which provides backdrop, card
  chrome, scroll lock, escape, click-outside, and the mount animation.

  Informational handoff (NOT a celebration): a logged-in user changed
  their EXISTING email; AccountsController#update held the change and
  emailed a confirmation link to the CURRENT (pre-change) address. This
  modal tells them to go click that link. The email does not change
  until they do.

  Distinct from modals/check_email on purpose — that one's copy says
  "finish entering" and its primary CTA dispatches a contest-board-only
  resend event. This modal has no Resend CTA and no contest wiring; a
  single "Got it" button closes via $store.modals.close().

  Single root element wrapping the template (the host mounts the
  registered partial through its own template x-if; multiple sibling
  roots there silently no-op). The x-data props reader is defined
  inline — no importmap factory.
%>
<div x-data="{ get props() { return ($store.modals.current() || {}).props || {} } }">
  <%= render 'modals/blocks/card_header',
        icon_emoji: '📬',
        title: 'Confirm your email change' do %>
    We sent a confirmation link to
    <span class="text-heading font-medium" x-text="props.currentEmail"></span>
    (your current address). Click the link in that email to confirm changing your
    email to
    <span class="text-heading font-medium" x-text="props.newEmail"></span>.
    Your email won't change until you do — the link expires in 30 minutes.
  <% end %>
  <button @click="$store.modals.close()"
          class="btn btn-primary btn-lg w-full">Got it</button>
</div>
